OL,3,CRow breaks out over number of rough
OL,4,Csleepers on the streets
OL,6,F"However, this way of estimating the
OL,7,Fnumber of rough sleepers is almost by
OL,8,Fdefinition an underestimate as in
OL,9,Forder to count, a rough sleeper must
OL,10,Fbe observed either bedded down or
OL,11,Fabout to bed down on the night. This
OL,12,Fsounds fine, but it means anyone
OL,13,Fsleeping rough who is not located by
OL,14,Fthe team doesn't get counted, and
OL,15,Fanyone not bedding down or about to
OL,16,Fbed down when they are seen doesn't
OL,17,Fget counted either, even if they are
OL,18,Fknown to be sleeping rough.
OL,26,@nD@AOU
